[head=3][bold]Charges[/bold][/head]
╔═══════════════════════════════╗

╚═══════════════════════════════╝

[color=SteelBlue]▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪

[head=2]Pronouncement[/head][/color]

Command members, by stamping this form, you certify that you believe that it is in the greatest interest of the station that the Captain named above is removed from office, and that the charges brought against the Captain are valid, and that they are likely guilty of the crimes they are being charged with. For the purpose of this form, you don't have to be certain of the Captain's guilt, it is only required that you think it is more likely than not that they are guilty.

[color=SteelBlue]▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪  ▪

[head=2]Procedure[/head][/color]

1) After all Station Command members besides the Captain have stamped this form, a copy must be sent to both Central Command and the Head of Personnel's office for storage. 

2) Station Command shall then immediately hold a meeting to elect an Interim Captain.

3) In the same meeting, after an Interim Captain is elected, Station Command will delegate either a member of the Security Team or a member of Station Command that isn't the Interim Captain with the responsibility to compile evidence and prepare the prosecuting case against the former Captain. It is recommended that the Head of Security.

4) The Interim Captain will serve until the trial. The former Captain will have their access equal that of a Passenger, and their Job Title should be set to, "Abeyant Captain." They are not to be arrested and sent to the brig unless they refuse to relinquish their authority until the trial, or they commit further crimes while they remain Abeyant. An Abeyant Captain that is arrested for a Felony or Capital crime shall be arrested until their Trial date, and if found guilty at Trial, the the crimes they will be sentenced to at minimum Extended Confinement.

5) A bench trial shall be held, with the Captain as the defense, and the previously delegated individual as the prosecution. The Interim Captain is only allowed at the Trial if they are needed as a witness, and shall only enter the courtroom when they are being called upon, and leave the courtroom once they are relieved. The Presiding Judge for the case shall be a representative of Central Command, or a crew member of the station selected by Central Command. During the trial, the Presiding Judge shall hold complete authority over the courtroom, the Abeyant Captain, and the Prosecutor.

6) Once the Trial concludes, if the Captain is found innocent, then the Interim Captain shall step down, the original Captain shall regain authority, and the Captain will be unable to be charged or impeached for any of the crimes that were alleged from this trial, including any alleged crimes from their time as the Abeyant Captain. If the Captain is found guilty, they are to be sentenced for their crimes according to space law. Furthermore, if Central Command does not appoint a new Captain within 24 hours of the former Captain being found guilty, the Interim Captain shall permanently become the new Captain, graduating from their interim status.

[color=SteelBlue]──────────────────────────────────────[/color]

[color=Gray]This form is only valid when stamped by all present and living members of Station Command besides the Captain.[/color]
